assessments.note:
This is a simple and elegant solution which avoids big problems such as waste of time, which reduce productivity and discourage members, uneven reviews, which reduce the overall fund's confidence, etc.
However, there are 4 things that can be evaluated by you and may be helpful for the proposal:
a.	Add what you expect to reach with these KPI: E.g. What do we (community) expect to see as a result of 20% engagement in the tool by C.A;
b.	Add a "homogeneity metric" as KPI: One of the problems described was the uneven reviews, therefore if with the use of the tool this parameter gets better, we could associate this evolution with the tool;
c.	Add another filter to C.A.'s tool: If there is a possibility to add a required knowledge in order to avoid waste of time by them (mainly by newcomers to this world). This way someone with low knowledge could be confident trying every challenge without worrying receiving something out of reach. Maybe it would be easier to implement this if this kind of information starts in the proposal itself;
d.	Try to implement a correlation of access and time in the proposal page to account as 'assessed': Imagine if there is lots of people who decides analyze and write their comments in other app (word or excel, eg) and only in the final days starts to pass it to the platform itself. Thus, the aim of eliminate the discrepancy among the proposals may not be achieved.
